annotation.TEXT: Whoops. Almost forgot about that hidden 1♥P. Okay, let's defeat Morton in less than 2 seconds flat!

Whoa, hello! Hitting the green block changes me into Luica! And then, hitting the yellow block changes me back into Marina! Man, if only I had known these were here earlier, I would've given Luica some screen time...
Yep, that flower sure came in handy alright...
Maybe that should say, "THE WIND IS VERY VERY STRONG.", instead of "A WIND IS VERY VERY STRONG." (replacing "A" with "THE").
Hah. No OMNOMNOM for those munchers today!
Nah, I've already filled out the map there, so I won't get lost. However, it is interesting the number of different paths that are available in world 4.
And, that's it for the castle revisiting. Now it's finally time to look at those voting results...

Okay, I think that's enough sightseeing here.
Now, I didn't find any hidden blocks out here besides the note block and the 1♥P block above it.

It's interesting how the game keeps track of the individual characters' bonus stars and score. But, I wonder why that's not also the case with coins, lives, and power ups? Also, shouldn't the Marina block be red, not yellow?
Oh, no. It's this section that gave raocow tons of trouble. Let's see how I fare...
Oh, yeah. This is world 5, so of course there'll be wind. Also, this appears to be a vertical level.
Huh. That was interesting how Larry dropped straight down off the edge there.
Well anyway, this unlocks 9-5, so now every world 9 level is unlocked! Yay! Now let's go around and see what levels you guys can vote on for next time...
Why did I end up getting all jittery there? I wasn't jittery like that anywhere else, even with wind pushing me into ceilings in various other places...
Alright, that's plenty good. Now, let's take down Lemmy once again!
Uh, oh. Updrafts into upside-down boiling grape juice, because that's totally how physics works. Just run through these.
Whoa. Good thing I had that shell. Umm... Camera? Little help here?
Neat.

If I'm rapidly pressing the Select button as the title screen resets... (This takes several seconds... I forget how long exactly...)

*Goes and checks* ...No, surprisingly. I looked around and there doesn't seem to be anything else over there, and the screen stops scrolling up about right where I was, so was there any special meaning to those two single coin blocks?
Ooh, a 1♥P. Now, what if I didn't hit that turn block in time?
Alright, here I am on the NES SMB3 title screen. Now, when the menu appears, you can press Select to move the cursor, just like this.
Yep, it's a flower alright. Might come in handy against Larry.
And the victory music starts at exactly 400 on the clock. That's interesting, and gets Luica a free 1♥P (which is useless), because she has 0 bonus stars.
Awesome. Also, I guess you can climb on the shorter fence if you duck-jump and glide onto it while holding up.

And there you go. There's 11 levels there. Place your votes and we'll find out where I head next time! Also, if anyone remembers which level(s) had message box(es) that I haven't checked in English yet, let me know! To be continued...

Oh! I had forgotten that I had hit midpoint here when I replayed this level back then, but then I didn't fully complete it the second time! That's convenient! Can I get ahold of a shell so that I can skip the second half again?
